We derived cortical gradients separately from structural and functional connectivity matrices, using diffusion map embedding. This identifies spatial axes of variation in connectivity across different areas, whereby cortical vertices that are strongly interconnected are closer together and vertices with little or no inter-connectivity are farther apart45,46. We used normalised angle as a metric of similarity (values between 0 and 1, with 1 denoting identical angles, and 0 opposing angles). The normalised angle between two nodes i and j (A(i, j)) is calculated as shown in equation 1 below:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
